  "title": "chore: setup scheduled release",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR sets up scheduled release. And it additionally upgrades `ship.js` to the latest version and updated some configs due to the breaking changes from `ship.js`.\r\n\r\nWe can periodically release the newer version of the library. And I hope to get rid of unnecessary communication like:\r\n\r\n> Can I release this today? Any blocker?\r\n\r\nInstead, the pull request will be created automatically, and as reviewers, we can address any blocker in the pull request if there is any.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nEvery Tuesday 09:00 UTC (11am Paris), `shipjs prepare` will run and create a release pull-request.\r\nIf there is a patch update and there is no `fix` commit, then it will skip.",
